everarch - the hopefully ever lasting archive

1) Build
2) Tests
3) License


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Build

On linux you can execute the following within the everarch directory
to build the application.

$ cmake .
$ make


------------------------------------------------------------------------
Tests

Build the application and then exectute the following to run the whole
test suite:

$ ./test.sh

Test execution relies on valgrind ( https://www.valgrind.org ).

The following steps should be performed when adding new tests. We
assume a test for x.h/x.c should be added.

Create a file which should contain the tests beside x.c with the name
x-test.c. Add a main function which tests x.h and x.c.

Open CMakeLists.txt and add a section like this one:

add_executable(x-test
  src/assert.c
  src/x.c
  src/x-test.c
  )
target_link_libraries(x-test
  ${CJSON_LIBRARIES}
  ${SQLite3_LIBRARIES}
  )
add_test(x-test ./x-test)

Execute `cmake .` in the root project so ctest will recognize the new
test.


